race.comment: Plenty of punters will be watching COSMIC CRUSADER (3) with intent as he looks to book his spot in next week's G1 Railway. He needs to win this to get in and may have just felt the pinch late first-up in the Asian Beau when not beaten far. Fitter now and his SP there suggested he's right up to winning a race of this calibre. BONJOY (4) was in the bunched finish of the Asian Beau where she closed off nicely from midfield. This shapes similarly and she's known to peak third-up in the past. Expected to be in the finish. Keeping a close eye on STORYVILLE (11) who is already in the Railway next week. She's been ticking along nicely and now gets Pike in the saddle third-up. Plenty to like about her down in the weights. MULTINATIONAL (10) just missed in the Northam Cup to show his Hannans win wasn't a fluke. Not out of this on recent efforts. LUVNWAR (9) can be in the finish again after jumping favourite in this race 12 months ago.
